In view of the above noted audit issues, we recommended the following:
 The Management submit a copy of a duly approved Local School Board Budget as well as justification as to the reason for the failure to submit said budget on time despite various verbal and written demand made; and
 Submit the above noted lacking supporting documents in order to determine the validity of the charges made;

We recommended that the Management:
 Justify the non-provision for the procurement of disaster preparedness equipment, non-conduct of vulnerability and adaptation assessment, procurement of rice other than from NFA as well as the discrepancy in the status of the unexpended/unobligated balance of the LDRRMF in the previous years;
 Provide the liquidation documents for the received in-kind goods and locally procured goods amounting to ₱928,315.00;
 Improve the internal control system of the LGU in order to ensure that the PPAs charged to the fund are for LDRRM related activities and that all supporting documents are attached to the disbursement vouchers;
 Ensure that all charges to the fund follow the required disbursement process so as to lessen various internal control weaknesses noted;
 See to it that unexpended/ unobligated funds from prior years LDRRM are treated as Trust Liability at the end of the year and duly transferred to a special trust fund account;
 Utilize the prior years’ trust liability for the acquisition of disaster preparedness equipment as well as immediate assistance and services to calamity-stricken constituents; and
 Henceforth, provide in the Notes to Financial Statements all the required disclosures as mandated under COA Circular No. 2014-002.

We have recommended that management justify the noted lapses. Submit the required supporting documents, if any. Henceforth, the following should also be implemented:
 The Municipal Accountant and Treasurer require the submission of an irrevocable standby letter of credit or surety bond before the release of the 15% Mobilization Fee and Retention Money;
 The Municipal Engineer Designate should ensure that the required materials and quality tests to ensure the quality of the works of the contractors be made mandatory;
 The inspectorate committee and/or the Municipal Engineer Designate see to it that a project monitoring system be implemented so as to determine whether the contractors had already incurred negative slippage; and
 The Management to forfeit the performance security of the contractors on account of delayed implementation of projects.

In view of the above noted lapses, we have recommended that:
 The Municipal Accountant justify the payment of the transactions despite the absence of the BAC Resolution recommending the mode of procurement used and award of the contract;
 The concerned Department Heads should justify the use of unsigned RFQ;
 The Municipal Mayor justify entering into contract without the concurrence of the majority of the BAC; and
 The management identifies the method of procurement used and justifies the non-conduct of competitive public bidding.

In view of the noted lapses, we have recommended the following:
a) The MSWDO being the leading authority in identifying gender related issues and concerns, see to it that GAD activities are identified through the use of HGDG and GAD Database, that the GAD plan are regularly updated and that the identified projects do address the GAD issues and concern in the long run; 
b) The GFPS see to it that the related GAD Plan and budget are endorsed by the PPDO and DILG. Any changes made thereof should be approved by the said agencies and properly reflected in the revised GAD Plan and Budget; 
c) The Management sees to it that the GAD Accomplishment Report would be complete and subjected to HGDG. Said Accomplishment report should tally with the reports provided by the Municipal Accountant and/or Budget Officer; 
d) Henceforth, management see to it that the GAD Activities implemented addresses the GAD Objectives and cause of the gender issue identified; and 
e) Management henceforth should familiarize themselves with the relevant promulgations with regards to the preparation and implementation of a duly approved GAD Plan and Budget.

