In view of the above noted lapses in the partial/full implementation of BUB projects, we have recommended the following:

The Municipal Mayor instructs the responsible officials to justify the noted lapses.  The detailed engineering designs, permits and surveys cited in the preceding paragraphs should be submitted immediately for review and evaluation. The required tests of the infrastructure projects should also be conducted in compliance with the said DILG Memorandum Circular;
The Municipal Mayor instruct the Municipal Accountant and Treasurer to submit disbursement vouchers including its required supporting schedules on time so as to provide ample time for the audit team to request inspection of the infrastructure projects;
The Municipal Mayor instruct the project focal person to coordinate with the Department of Health to secure copy of the MOA or fund utilization guidelines of the project; and 
The Municipal Mayor instruct the project focal person for the implementation of BUB project for CY 2016 to provide supporting documents that the revision in the project description was duly approved by the DBM, otherwise said amount shall be disallowed in audit.

We have recommended the following:
That the Budget Officer and Accountant justify the non-maintenance of the required registries, failure to duly accomplish the required obligation request as well as the non-submission of SAAOB;
That the Budget Officer coordinate with the Accountant and Municipal Treasurer in the preparation and submission of the reconciliation statement of SCBAA the soonest possible time so as to allow the audit team to have ample time to verify the same;
The Municipal Mayor instructs the Budget Officer and different department heads to strictly adhere to the budgetary and disbursement process; and
Henceforth, familiarize themselves and ensure strict compliance with the different budgetary requirements.

